{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"o5eWrN66S3f6N9dJ92oDy","title":"Hiring","vault":{"fsPath":"handbook","name":"dendron.handbook"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"summary":{"type":"header","text":"Summary","value":"summary","line":9,"column":0}},"fname":"handbook.people.hiring","updated":1629207313166,"created":1629207036757,"parent":"5e818073-c734-44a8-9bd5-1dbe6b78c3e9","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"f68387d4398f1da9f51dc504e12b1b7e","custom":{"nav_order":1}},"body":"<h1 id=\"hiring\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#hiring\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Hiring</h1>\n<h2 id=\"summary\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#summary\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Summary</h2>\n<p>Our hiring process changes depending on your history with Dendron. It consists of three phases:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>interview with the founder</li>\n<li>interview with the team</li>\n<li>2 week contracting gig</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you've been a regular contributor to one of our open source projects  and have done at least few <a href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/1e6c8b49-ef88-4e79-b2df-e9d614c38a53.html#medium\">medium</a> tasks, often we will skip the contracting part and hire you after the round of interviews. </p>\n<p>Otherwise, we'll do a paid two week contracting gig where you will be doing the same job as what you would when working with us full time. We find this is a much better way of evaluating fit than a coding screen and gives both us and you a chance to make sure we work well together. </p>","noteIndex":{"id":"27237fd0-4ae1-4e31-9c15-34167fb264d8","title":"Dendron Handbook","vault":{"fsPath":"handbook","name":"dendron.handbook"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{},"fname":"handbook","updated":1623260668267,"created":1610126185067,"parent":null,"children":["5c65d3b7-403c-49b2-8161-efb6